---
import DocsLayout from '@/layouts/DocsLayout.astro'
---
<DocsLayout
  title="Secrets Management"
  description="AES-256-GCM encrypted secrets stored safely in your repo, pushed to servers at deploy time."
  section="features"
>
  <p>
    Shuttle encrypts your app secrets with AES-256-GCM and stores the ciphertext in
    <code>.shuttle/secrets.enc</code>. The encryption key lives at <code>.shuttle/key</code> and
    never leaves your machine (or CI). You can safely commit <code>secrets.enc</code> to version
    control — without the key, it's useless. At deploy time, Shuttle decrypts and uploads secrets
    as a <code>.env</code> file on the server.
  </p>

  <h2>How it works</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>On first use, Shuttle generates a random 256-bit key at <code>.shuttle/key</code>.</li>
    <li>Each secret is stored as a key-value pair in the encrypted file <code>.shuttle/secrets.enc</code>.</li>
    <li>During deploy (steps 5/3 of blue-green/rolling), Shuttle decrypts and uploads secrets to <code>/opt/shuttle/&lt;app&gt;/&lt;app&gt;/.env</code> with mode <code>0600</code>.</li>
    <li>Containers receive secrets via <code>--env-file</code>.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>CLI commands</h2>

  <h3>shuttle secrets set</h3>
  <p>Encrypt and store a secret locally:</p>
  <pre><code class="language-bash">shuttle secrets set DATABASE_URL "postgres://user:pass@localhost/mydb"
shuttle secrets set REDIS_URL "redis://localhost:6379"
shuttle secrets set API_SECRET_KEY "super-secret-value"
</code></pre>

  <h3>shuttle secrets get</h3>
  <p>Decrypt and print a single secret value:</p>
  <pre><code class="language-bash">shuttle secrets get DATABASE_URL
# postgres://user:pass@localhost/mydb
</code></pre>

  <h3>shuttle secrets list</h3>
  <p>List all secret keys (values are not shown):</p>
  <pre><code class="language-bash">shuttle secrets list
# DATABASE_URL
# REDIS_URL
# API_SECRET_KEY
</code></pre>

  <h3>shuttle secrets remove</h3>
  <p>Remove a secret from the encrypted store:</p>
  <pre><code class="language-bash">shuttle secrets remove API_SECRET_KEY
</code></pre>

  <h3>shuttle secrets push</h3>
  <p>Manually push secrets to a server (also happens automatically on every deploy):</p>
  <pre><code class="language-bash">shuttle secrets push
</code></pre>

  <h2>File layout</h2>
  <pre><code class="language-bash">.shuttle/
  key           # 256-bit AES key — NEVER commit this
  secrets.enc   # AES-256-GCM ciphertext — safe to commit
</code></pre>

  <h2>Configuration</h2>
  <p>
    The secrets block in <code>shuttle.yml</code> specifies the file path and driver:
  </p>
  <pre><code class="language-yaml">secrets:
  file: .shuttle/secrets.enc   # path to the encrypted store (default)
  driver: aes                  # encryption driver (default: aes)
</code></pre>

  <h2>Security model</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>AES-256-GCM</strong> provides authenticated encryption — tampering with the ciphertext is detected.</li>
    <li>The key file uses mode <code>0600</code> and should only be readable by your user.</li>
    <li>On the server, the <code>.env</code> file is written with mode <code>0600</code> and owned by the deploy user.</li>
    <li>Secrets are never logged or printed by Shuttle.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What to commit vs what not to</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>File</th>
        <th>Commit?</th>
        <th>Why</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><code>.shuttle/secrets.enc</code></td>
        <td>Yes</td>
        <td>Encrypted ciphertext — useless without the key</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>.shuttle/key</code></td>
        <td><strong>Never</strong></td>
        <td>The encryption key — keep it secret, back it up separately</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <p>
    Add this to your <code>.gitignore</code>:
  </p>
  <pre><code class="language-bash">.shuttle/key
.shuttle/certs/
</code></pre>

  <h2>Using secrets in CI</h2>
  <p>
    Store the contents of <code>.shuttle/key</code> as a CI secret (e.g., <code>SHUTTLE_KEY</code>),
    then restore it before running <code>shuttle deploy</code>:
  </p>
  <pre><code class="language-bash">mkdir -p .shuttle
echo "$SHUTTLE_KEY" > .shuttle/key
chmod 600 .shuttle/key
shuttle deploy
</code></pre>
</DocsLayout>
